Var(x\pm y)=Var(x)+Var(y)
E[X^2]-(E[X])^2=Var(X)
Var(x \pm y)= Var(x)+Var(y)\pm 2(E[XY]-E[X]E[Y])
X
Y
Var(X\pm Y)=Var(X)+ Var(Y)\pm 2Cov(X,Y)
Cov(X,Y)=0
X
Y
X
Y
E(XY)=E(X)E(Y)
\text{Var}(aX+bY) = \text{Cov}(aX+bY,aX+bY)=a\text{Cov}(X,aX+bY)+b\text{Cov}(Y,aX+bY)
=a^2\text{Cov}(X,X)+ab\text{Cov}(X,Y)+ab\text{Cov}(Y,X)+b^2\text{Cov}(Y,Y)
=a^2\text{Var}(X) + b^2\text{Var}(Y) + 2ab\text{Cov}(X,Y)
\text{Cov}(X,Y) \stackrel{\text{def}}{=} \text{E}(XY) - \text{E}(X)\text{E}(Y)
\text{Var}(X)\stackrel{\text{def}}{=}\text{Cov}(X,X)
\boxed{\text{Var}(aX+bY) = a^2\text{Var}(X) + b^2\text{Var}(Y) + 2ab\text{Cov}(X,Y)}
a=1
b=\pm 1
